==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tom
<hw>Tom</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The knave of trumps at
gleek.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tom</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tom
<hw>Tom</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A familiar contraction of
<altname>Thomas</altname>, a proper name of a man.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The male of certain animals; -- often used
adjectively or in composition; <as>as, <ex>tom</ex> turkey,
<ex>tom</ex>cat, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tomahawk</ent>⟦br⟧
